The paper discusses a remote user authentication scheme for multi-server environments, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The scheme uses self-certified public keys, which involves the use of cryptography and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the vulnerabilities of previous schemes and proposes improvements, which involves the study of cyber threats and countermeasures (cs.CY), software engineering (cs.SE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
